com.ualberta.cmput301w17t22.moodswing

Class Participant

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ualberta.cmput301w17t22.moodswing.User
      • com.ualberta.cmput301w17t22.moodswing.Participant

  • public class Participant
extends User
    A Participant is an end user of the app and is uniquely identified by their username.

    The Participant holds all the information about a user; all of their mood events, their followers, who they are following, etc.

    Version:
    2017-03-03
    Author:
    Fred
    See Also:
    User, MoodEvent, ApprovalList

        public void followParticipant(Participant receivingParticipant)
        Follow a participant by: Checking if the sending participant is in their block list. Checks to see if the sending participant has already sent a follow request to that participant. Checks to see if the sending participant is already following the participant. Successfully follows a participant by: Adding the participant to the sending participants pending on the followingList. Creates a follower request that is sent to the receiving participant.
